Parliament, Thursday, 8 October 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Environment, Forestry and Fisheries has been informed that its member, Ms Simphiwe Mbatha, has been admitted at hospital last night.
	
	The committee wishes her a speedy recovery from her high care hospitalisation and is looking forward to seeing her back at her home and to continue with the work of the committee which is very close to her heart.
	
	The Chairperson of the committee, Mr Fikile Xasa, said: “We trust that honourable Mbatha is going to overcome this temporary course of illness and regain her healthy life soon by God’s ever-present grace. We will unceasingly pray for her full recovery.”
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON ENVIRONMENT, FORESTRY AND FISHERIES, MR FIKILE XASA.
	
